sub_title: Key Account Manager Horticultural Projects at Bayer Crop Science
summary:
As son of a rose farmer, I was grown up in Naaldwijk and located in the center of the Dutch horticulture industry. After graduating from the Rotterdam University (Commercial Economics), I started my professional career at Priva, later on moved to Monsanto and finally transitioned to Bayer Vegetables Seeds. Currently almost 10 years of professional experience in different sales and international new business development positions. 

Still on the move to partner with new vegetable lovers in the global high-tech greenhouse industry =)
